  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Implementation of Social Cohesion Activities in Mayukwayukwa and Meheba Local Integration Sites</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to strengthen social cohesion to foster tolerant, inclusive and integrated resettlement communities. The key interventions for this project include supporting training and sensitization on civic education, gender based violence (GBV), violence against children, and political rights; establishment of anti-GBV task forces; and creation of women and children/youths&apos; platforms to promote their active participation in addressing their rights and mounting support against child marriages. In order to promote community cohesion, activities include support towards the establishment of age and gender specific groups to challenge negative community norms, creation of communal spaces that promote cohesion and interaction, promoting access to community events such as local sports leagues, joint cultural events, national holiday celebrations and commemorations, and promoting inclusion of women and youth in leadership and management roles. The project also supports conducting a rapid assessment on child marriage and other forms of violence, and the development of a communication strategy on individual rights and responsibilities and aspects of violence, abuse and exploitation. The strategy will inform subsequent phases of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
